---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/ui/CTASection.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/ui/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import TestimonialsSection from '../../components/sections/TestimonialsSection.astro';

const city = "Saddle River";
const title = "CPA in Saddle River NJ | Tax & Accounting Services | ProAxis";
const description = "ProAxis offers expert CPA services in Saddle River NJ — high-net-worth tax planning, investment portfolio taxation, and multi-state residency planning. 100% virtual.";
const canonical = "/service-areas/saddle-river/";
const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Service Areas", url: "/service-areas/" },
  { name: city }
];
const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": ["LocalBusiness", "AccountingService"],
  "name": "ProAxis Tax & Accounting Services",
  "telephone": "+12018002330",
  "email": "info@proaxiscpa.com",
  "url": "https://proaxiscpa.com",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Hasbrouck Heights",
    "addressRegion": "NJ",
    "postalCode": "07604",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": { "@type": "City", "name": "Saddle River, NJ" }
};
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description} {canonical} {schema} {breadcrumbs}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1C1C1E 0%, #2E75B6 100%);" class="py-14 lg:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold mb-4" style="background-color: rgba(197,165,90,0.2); color: #C5A55A;">
        Serving {city}, NJ &bull; 100% Virtual
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold font-heading text-white mb-4">CPA &amp; Accounting Services in {city}, NJ</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-8">ProAxis delivers expert tax preparation, tax planning, bookkeeping, and business advisory to {city} businesses and residents — all virtually, all on your schedule.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-white" style="background-color: #22C55E;">Schedule Free Consultation</a>
        <a href="tel:+12018002330" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-white border-2 border-white/40">Call (201) 800-2330</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 lg:py-16">

    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">About Saddle River's Business &amp; Tax Landscape</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Saddle River is one of New Jersey's most exclusive residential communities, a borough of approximately 3,000 residents that has deliberately preserved its character through large minimum lot sizes, extensive equestrian trails, and a near-complete absence of commercial development. Horse farms, compound-style estates, and wooded properties define the landscape — making Saddle River feel more like a private rural retreat than a Bergen County suburb. The borough consistently ranks among the highest per-capita income communities in New Jersey, and its residents include retired executives, active Wall Street professionals, real estate developers, entertainment figures, and celebrities who value the privacy this enclave affords.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Because Saddle River has almost no commercial base, the tax and financial advisory work here centers entirely on individual wealth management and personal financial complexity. Residents typically have investment portfolios spanning multiple asset classes — publicly traded securities, private equity fund interests, real estate limited partnerships, hedge fund investments, and alternative assets. Managing the tax implications of each of these requires proactive <a href="/tax-services/tax-planning/" class="font-medium underline" style="color: #2E75B6;">tax planning strategies</a> throughout the year, not a single annual review in the spring. Qualified dividends and long-term capital gains receive preferential federal tax rates, but New Jersey taxes all investment income at ordinary rates — a distinction that materially affects after-tax returns and must be factored into portfolio rebalancing decisions.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Many Saddle River residents maintain homes in multiple states — a Florida condominium for winter months, a summer property in the Hamptons or on the Jersey Shore, perhaps a ski chalet in Vermont or Colorado. Multi-state residency planning is a significant tax discipline in its own right. NJ's "domicile" rules determine where you are legally taxed as a resident, and the standards are more nuanced than simply counting days. Audit risk from the NJ Division of Taxation for high-income individuals who claim domicile elsewhere while maintaining a New Jersey home is real and meaningful. ProAxis helps Saddle River clients document their domicile position rigorously and structure their activities to support their intended state of residency.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">For those Saddle River residents who are general partners, managing members, or active investors in business ventures — real estate development partnerships, operating businesses, or investment funds — our <a href="/business-services/" class="font-medium underline" style="color: #2E75B6;">business advisory services</a> provide the entity-level accounting, NJ BAIT election analysis, and Schedule K-1 reconciliation that these structures require. Passive activity rules under IRC Section 469 frequently limit the deductibility of losses from real estate and other passive investments, and understanding how to maximize deductible losses within those rules is an important planning lever for Saddle River investors.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">Saddle River Tax Considerations</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The wealth profile of Saddle River residents generates a distinct set of tax challenges that reward careful, year-round attention. Here are the issues most frequently relevant to Saddle River clients:</p>
    <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-6">
      {[
        { heading: "Qualified dividend and long-term capital gain rate optimization", text: "Federal preferential rates on qualified dividends (0%, 15%, or 20%) and long-term capital gains can be optimized through careful timing of asset sales, tax-loss harvesting to offset gains, and asset location strategies across taxable and tax-deferred accounts." },
        { heading: "NJ property tax strategy", text: "Saddle River properties carry substantial assessed values and corresponding property tax bills. While the federal SALT deduction cap limits the federal benefit of these payments, proper documentation and any available NJ property tax credits should still be maximized." },
        { heading: "Multi-state residency and domicile planning", text: "Saddle River residents with homes in multiple states need a clear, defensible domicile position. Day counts, center-of-life documentation, and the location of primary professional and personal activities all matter in a residency audit." },
        { heading: "FBAR and FATCA for international investments", text: "Residents with foreign financial accounts exceeding $10,000 at any point during the year must file FinCEN Form 114 (FBAR). FATCA Form 8938 has separate but overlapping thresholds. Penalties for non-compliance are severe — proactive disclosure is always the right approach." },
        { heading: "Passive activity loss rules for real estate investors", text: "Losses from real estate limited partnerships and passive investments are generally deductible only against passive income. Real estate professional status under IRC Section 469 can change this equation significantly for Saddle River residents with material real estate holdings." },
      ].map((item) => (
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 rounded-lg" style="background-color: #F7F8FA;">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #C5A55A;"></div>
          <div><span class="font-semibold" style="color: #1C1C1E;">{item.heading}:</span> <span class="text-gray-700">{item.text}</span></div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>

    <!-- ProAxis Services -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 mb-10" style="background-color: #F7F8FA;">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">ProAxis Serves Saddle River Residents &amp; Investors</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">ProAxis Tax &amp; Accounting Services provides high-net-worth individual tax planning, investment income reporting, and estate coordination services to Saddle River residents. Our fully virtual model delivers the same quality as a top-tier Manhattan or Midtown firm, with the accessibility and responsiveness of a local Bergen County CPA practice. No traffic, no parking, no waiting rooms — just expert advice when you need it.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mt-5">
        {[
          { name: "Business Services", link: "/business-services/" },
          { name: "Tax Planning & Strategy", link: "/tax-services/tax-planning/" },
          { name: "Tax Preparation", link: "/tax-services/tax-preparation/" },
          { name: "Bookkeeping", link: "/business-services/bookkeeping/" },
          { name: "NJ SALT Consulting", link: "/tax-services/nj-salt-consulting/" },
          { name: "Fractional CFO", link: "/business-services/fractional-cfo/" },
        ].map((svc) => (
          <a href={svc.link} class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 font-medium transition-all" style="color: #2E75B6;">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
            </svg>
            {svc.name}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">Investment Portfolio Tax Management for Saddle River Residents</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Saddle River residents with substantial investment portfolios face a challenge that many simpler taxpayers do not: the interaction between federal and New Jersey tax treatment of investment income is materially different, and decisions that appear optimal at the federal level may produce suboptimal NJ outcomes — or vice versa. NJ taxes all investment income at ordinary income rates, does not recognize the Section 1202 small business stock exclusion, and has its own separate capital gains calculation rules. A tax plan that only accounts for federal rates leaves money on the table.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Tax-loss harvesting is a year-round discipline for portfolio-heavy Saddle River clients. By systematically recognizing losses in underperforming positions and using them to offset capital gains elsewhere in the portfolio, we can reduce current-year tax liability without fundamentally altering the investment strategy. Wash sale rules require careful attention during this process — ProAxis tracks these positions throughout the year rather than discovering them at tax time.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">For Saddle River residents who receive Schedule K-1s from partnerships, S-corporations, or trusts, the annual tax return is only as accurate as the K-1 reconciliation process. K-1s frequently arrive late, contain errors, or require adjustments based on prior-year basis tracking. ProAxis maintains detailed basis schedules for each pass-through investment and coordinates the K-1 reconciliation process to ensure accurate reporting and maximize available deductions.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold font-heading mb-5" style="color: #1C1C1E;">Nearby Areas We Also Serve</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">ProAxis serves individuals and families throughout Bergen County's most prestigious communities. If you are near Saddle River, we also work with clients in:</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-8">
      {[
        { name: "Alpine", slug: "alpine" },
        { name: "Upper Saddle River", slug: "upper-saddle-river" },
        { name: "Wyckoff", slug: "wyckoff" },
        { name: "Ho-Ho-Kus", slug: "ho-ho-kus" },
      ].map((area) => (
        <a href={`/service-areas/${area.slug}/`} class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-medium border hover:shadow-sm transition-all" style="border-color: #2E75B6; color: #2E75B6; background-color: rgba(46,117,182,0.05);">{area.name}</a>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Ready to put proactive tax planning to work for your Saddle River household? <a href="/contact/" class="font-medium underline" style="color: #2E75B6;">Schedule a free consultation</a> with ProAxis today, or explore our <a href="/tax-services/" class="font-medium underline" style="color: #2E75B6;">complete tax services</a> and <a href="/business-services/" class="font-medium underline" style="color: #2E75B6;">business accounting services</a>.</p>
  </article>

  <TestimonialsSection />
  <CTASection heading={"CPA Services in " + city + ", NJ — Schedule Your Free Consultation"} />
</BaseLayout>
